<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Since it is fairly obvious that Mythic intends to fix defficiant spell lines after class bugs, it would make sense to start thinking about matter line ideas early and hopefully come up with spells that would properly define a matter spec sorc from other casters.<P>Right now our matter spec gives us a more powerful DoT, higher damage and more ticks.  However, as you get higher most mobs die fairly quickly with a good group anyway. In RvR DoT works great on a lone archer but just doesn't do much damage to them at an even level.<P>So this brings us to my first spell idea-<BR>Right now we have the acid "cloud" in our base line, but it really isn't a "cloud" in the literal sence of the word. Why not make the matter spec DoT a real cloud, ie. area of effect. Perhaps drop the damage if this would be too overpowering, but as the way the spell is listed it makes perfect sense as a "cloud" that manages to stay just over one person is pretty unrealistic.<P>I have other ideas, but before I put them down, I'd like to know what exactly the matter line is supposed to be. Could you please help with that i3ullseye?<P>~Xiem Fightbearer<BR>Shining Force, Lancelot
</FONT>
