ok, follow me on this. this gave me a great idea. <P>ever hunt giants with a gorup and have people scream how horrible their frame rate gets when you debuff a giant? How they can't see a thing?<P>What if we literally generated a fairly large cloud that did minimal damage, maybe 5 per tick at the highest, merely a nuisance. but it woudl obscure vision? yeah a big green floating cloud of mist that limted vision for up to 20 seconds at a time?<P>Could have some real nice battlefield uses. Especially when you want to roll that seige engine into place during daylight without having your crew being sniped off.<P>lay it on top that fort wall and let's see those archers target your troops then!   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
