Heh, I have to say I don't really understand the argument "that's a cabalist thing" given all the other classes that have pets, that can mez, that can confuse, etc.  Seems to me the only way something gets defining is if it is the BEST version of that thing in the realm.  So, for example Sorcs have the BEST Mez, Therugists have the BEST bladeturn, so Cabalists can have the BEST Ae Dot.  Doesn't mean that Sorcs can't have AN Ae Dot.  Of course, you might not want an AE dot in a spec line that isn't optimal, but I'd argue that it's the recastable pet that makes the Cabalist unique anyway, in the same way it's been argued that it's the charmable pet that makes the Sorc unique.  If so, then Sorcs should be free to have optimal AE dot.
</FONT>
