I'm not especially keen on the idea of an AE DOT, it would only be useful in RvR, as the last thing this two hits and I'm dead sorcerer needs is to increase aggro on a whole area of creatures, not to mention justifiably upsetting the cabalists.  My preference would be a spell that would be useful in and out of realm battle.<P>  I like the idea of some kind of fog cloud, but on behalf of some poor friends with computers that can't handle the refresh rate increase from a minstrel&#8217;s speed song, I better mention that it could very easily make RvR impossible for some.<BR>  My twist on the fog idea would simply be an area of effect darkness spell.  Possibly cause the area to be slightly darker than nighttime for the enemy.  Essentially the same effect since the enemy could barely see their way around, but no extra graphics so no frame rate hit.  It may even increase their frame rate.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>  Something to think about though.  Would we get realm points for this contribution to the battle?<P>-Sage &lt;The Hing&gt; (Lancelot)
