<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I kinda like the idea of an AoE DOT of sorts.  But instead of hitting all creatures in the area with a single target DOT, I think it would be fun if each time the DOT pulsed, all enemies in the original AoE got hit.  Basically a cloud that damages anyone who stays in the area.<P>And while we're talking Matter spells, anyone else think the spec Matter DOT should be a little more useful, especially since we can't stack it?  I'd like it to delivery its damage in 16 seconds instead of 24, using eight 2-second pulses instead of six 4-second ones.  I'd probably want the base line DOT to be slightly more mana efficent, but if you wanted damage fast (in addition to better interrupt potential in RvR) you'd go for the spec DOT.<P>Another option would be to have the damage per pulse increase, so the first pulse does the least damage and the last one does the most.  This would help for aggro control (a little) in that it gives other people more time to accumulate damage on the target before your DOT really kicks in.<P>Either way, at least the spec DOT wouldn't feel so similar to the base line.<P>-Zanthis
</FONT>
