Stellaris:<P>My wording might have been awkward, but I did actually think about the 'grief' portion you mentioned. I said specifically that ENEMIES cannnot walk through it. I did, however, immediately follow that up with a prohibition that NOONE could target or shoot through it, which is probably where your confusion came from.<P>As for the balancing, just put the spell on a timer, give it at LEAST a 3 second cast time, and also make it so that only one wall can be up at a time.<BR>------------------------------<BR>Here is another, albeit oddball suggestion that could probably be coded in less then 10 minutes.<P>Forced Run<P>When hit by this spell, the target will begin to run straight ahead at normal speed for 1,2,3,4 or 5 full seconds, determined by spell level. Target cannot perform any actions other then those normally performable during a run. (Essentially the game would press UP-ARROW for the character, and would lock all other movement keys including sit and jump)<P>The base line (7,13,21,30,42)is single target, 30 second timer, 2 second cast time, BOLT range.<P>The spec line (5,15,25,35,45) is an AoE spell, 1 minute timer, 3 second cast time, normal range.<P>This would be an odd combination of a fear, root, and stun spell. "That bow-user/bolt-caster aiming out of pet range? Pull 'em closer to you while rendering their ranged attacks useless at the same time." "That mob or enemy player just wont get off you or your cleric, and you dont want to risk a confuse or mindwipe? Send 'em away for a few precious seconds."<P>P.S. I edited the spell durations so that they would not be as long as normal stuns of near-equivalent levels.
