Abit off topic (dont mean to steal thread) but this is my opinion on fear/charm type spells in PvP: <P>There are already easy ways to grief ppl: ie.  players attacking players in combat w npcs/mobs...a much more sure method of griefing than say a fear spell or the suggested force run spell.  Personally, I would like to see them remove xp loss if you have taken any damage or suffered from a "mind control" or debuff from another player (Id also like them to implement some method of RP gain for use of mezzes/debuffs and even healing spells).  I do understand that they want to avoid some ppl from taking advantage of this as an xp exploit.. I think the way xp is lost in these situations needs to be reversed...so ppl can PvP uninhibitted in the frontiers or hunt in the frontiers for xp if they wish w/o fear of losing xp due to another player's ignorance/malice Im sure there will still be plenty of xp deaths to mobs and lots of deaths from the hands of enemy players.<P>--------------------<P>Anonymous 38 Sorc Anon Server
